  "prompt": "What is the stock purchase plan for Tesla motors?",
  "response": "Tesla, Inc. offers an Employee Stock Purchase Plan (ESPP) that allows eligible employees to buy shares of Tesla stock at a discount. Here are some key features of the plan:\n\n1. **Eligibility**: Generally available to full-time employees who meet specific criteria set by the company.\n\n2. **Enrollment Period**: Employees can enroll during designated enrollment periods, typically occurring a few times a year.\n\n3. **Purchase Price**: Shares are usually offered at a discount, often around 15% off the market price, which can be further enhanced through a lookback feature that allows employees to purchase at the lower of the stock price at the beginning or the end of the offering period.\n\n4. **Contribution Limits**: Employees can choose to contribute a percentage of their paycheck towards the purchase of stock, up to a maximum limit set by the company or IRS regulations.\n\n5. **Offering Period**: The offering period can vary, generally lasting between six months to two years.\n\n6. **Tax Implications**: Employees should be aware of the potential tax implications when they sell shares purchased through the ESPP, including capital gains taxes.\n\nFor accurate and detailed information, including specific terms and updates, it's advisable to check Tesla's official employee resources or consult their Human Resources department. Additionally, the company's Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) filings might provide more insights into their stock purchase plans.",
